# No AI Attribution in Commits or Pull Requests

Never add AI tool attribution to commit messages or pull request descriptions.

## Prohibited patterns

- `Made-with: Cursor`
- `Co-authored-by: Codex` / `Co-authored-by: OpenAI`
- `Generated with Codex` / `Created with Codex`
- `AI-assisted` / `Written by Codex`
- Any `Made-with:`, `Generated-by:`, or similar trailer

## Applies to

- Commit message subject lines
- Commit message bodies and trailers
- Pull request titles and descriptions

## What to do instead

Write a standard commit message describing what changed and why. If an AI tool would normally inject attribution, omit it entirely.
